gep.model

Class ChromosomeIndependentGeneTerminal<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gep.model.GeneElement<T>
      • gep.model.GeneTerminal<T>
        • gep.model.ChromosomeIndependentGeneTerminal<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The return type of the execution of this terminal
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EnvironmentDependendTerminal

    public abstract class ChromosomeIndependentGeneTerminal<T>
extends GeneTerminal<T>
    This class represents a gene terminal whose execution is independent from the chromosome it is included in. That means its apply method does not need the chromosome as a parameter.
    Author:
    Johannes Wortmann
